# local/ lab conventions

## Topology

1 spine + 2 leaves + 2 clients (`ixrd2l`). Configs in `local/configs/fabric/`. Lab name `srl-local`; Docker mgmt network **`clab`** (`CLAB_NETWORK=clab`).

## Compose (KtransToGrafana golden path)

`compose-base.yaml` + `compose-groups.generated.yaml` + `compose-limits.generated.yaml` (via `make up`).

Services: `alloy`, `gnmic`, `ktranslate_snmp_srl`, `ktranslate_flow`, `ktranslate_syslog`, `topology_exporter`.

- Groups: `groups/srl.env` ‚Üí `make generate` ‚Üí poller/discovery configs under `config/` + `state/`
- Discovery: `make discover GROUP=srl` (not `--snmp_discovery_on_start`)
- Custom SNMP profiles: `snmp-profiles/nokia/` ‚Üí mount `kentik_snmp/nokia/` (stock profiles stay in image); expect `nokia-srlinux.yml` after rediscover
- Alloy: `local/alloy/config.alloy` ‚Äî comments must be `//` only. Receives OTLP; scrapes Docker logs for Clos + sidecars (skips ktranslate ‚Äî those use `--tee_logs` OTLP); remaps gnmic LLDP ‚Üí `network_topology_edge_info`; stamps `deployment.host`
- gnmic: `local/gnmic/gnmic.yaml` (OTLP ‚Üí Alloy; includes `lldp_neighbors` subscribe)
- topology-exporter: `local/topology-exporter/config.yaml` ‚Äî Image: `make topology-exporter-image`
- NetBox Cloud: optional ‚Äî `scripts/netbox-populate.py` + `make netbox-sync` when `DISCOVERY_SOURCE=netbox` (`groups/srl.env.netbox.sample`); default sample uses CIDR + `update-snmp-targets.sh`

## Scripts

- LF line endings only (CRLF breaks bash under WSL).
- `update-snmp-targets.sh` ‚Äî /32 mgmt IPs into `groups/srl.env` TARGETS + regenerate
- `update-topology-targets.sh` ‚Äî rewrite topology-exporter `host:` lines + sync `tester_id`
- `netbox-bootstrap.sh` / `make netbox-sync` / `make netbox-sync-mgmt` ‚Äî populate NetBox Cloud + mgmt IPs for SNMP discovery
- `lab-path.sh` / `sync-clab-workdir.sh` / `clab.sh` ‚Äî when repo is on `/mnt/c`, mirror fabric to ext4 (`CLAB_EXT4_ROOT`) for clab deploy
- `apply-fabric-config.sh` / `make fabric-apply` / `make fabric-up` ‚Äî load `configs/fabric/*.cfg` (full fabric on ext4 workdir)
- `staggered-up.sh` ‚Äî default `make up` path: fabric nodes then collectors one-by-one (`LAB_STAGGER_SECS`, logs RAM)
- `stabilize-lab.sh` / `make stabilize` ‚Äî recover without `clab deploy --reconfigure` (start SRL, apply fabric, discover)
- `enable-snmp-srl.sh` ‚Äî minimal SNMP-only fallback (superseded by `fabric-apply` when full cfg is needed)
- `softflowd.sh` ‚Äî clients ‚Üí `ktranslate_flow:9995`
- `syslog-config.sh` ‚Äî `docker exec -i` + `sr_cli` ‚Üí `ktranslate_syslog:1514` (requires `system logging network-instance mgmt`)
- `snmp-trap-config.sh` ‚Äî SRL `trap-group ktranslate` via mgmt ‚Üí poller UDP `1620` / `public`
- `emit-events.sh` ‚Äî apply syslog+trap config, flap leaf client/spine links for real traps+syslog
- `events-loop.sh` ‚Äî background traps every 3m + emit-events every 5m (`make events-loop|events-stop|events-status`)
- `traffic.sh` ‚Äî ongoing client1‚Üîclient2 UDP workloads (steady 3M, burst 8M/20s, reverse 1M, ping 1/s); TCP iperf can stall, but short HTTP (join-app) works
- `join-app.sh` ‚Äî OTel Go HTTP client on client1 ‚Üí server on client2 (`172.17.0.2:8080`); traces ‚Üí `alloy:4317`
- `join-fault.sh` ‚Äî tc netem delay/loss on client eth1 for Investigation talk track
- `trap-gen.sh` ‚Äî synthetic SNMPv2c traps to poller (`make traps`)

## Operator commands

`make -C local up|up-parallel|down|status|stabilize|fabric-up|fabric-apply|sync-clab-workdir|traffic|traffic-stop|traffic-status|join-app|join-app-stop|join-app-status|join-fault|join-fault-stop|join-fault-status|events-loop|events-stop|events-status|logs|generate|discover|topology-exporter-image|topology-targets|netbox-sync|netbox-sync-mgmt` or root `make local-up`. Agents may use `wsl -e bash -lc '...'` from Windows.

**Agent rule:** never `clab deploy --reconfigure` unless the user explicitly requests it. Use `make stabilize` to recover stopped SRL nodes.

## WSL /mnt/c postdeploy

ContainerLab postdeploy cannot commit SR Linux config when startup-config/labdir are on drvfs (`/mnt/c/...`). `scripts/clab.sh` detects drvfs and deploys from `CLAB_EXT4_ROOT` (default `~/.cache/network-o11y-demo/clab`). Symptoms if bypassed: postdeploy ERRO; SNMP/BGP/EVPN missing. Fix: `make fabric-up`, `make fabric-apply`, or `make stabilize`.

## Topology metrics

- Devices: `network_topology_device_info` (exporter OTLP; `tester_id` from `LAB_TESTER_ID`, default `network-lab`)
- Edges: `network_topology_edge_info` (gnmic LLDP YANG ‚Üí Alloy remap; stock SRL SNMP has no LLDP rem-table)

